===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a deer with antlers.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructed this word's OC pronunciation as *''rêh'' and considered it a possible allofam of {{och-l|麗|tr=*rê(k)h}} "number" < "what is calculated", exopassive derivative of {{och-l|歷|tr=*rêk}} "to calculate".

{{lang|zh|麗}} underwent this historical semantic shift: from "a pair" ({{w|Rites of Zhou|Zhouli}}), to "mate, companion" ({{zh-l|*儷}}) ({{w|Zuozhuan|Zuo}}), to "paired", to "well-proportioned" ({{w|Book of Rites|Liji}}), and finally to "elegant, beautiful" ({{w|Chu Ci|Chuci}}) as well as "refinement" ({{w|Book of Documents|Shu}}).

